  "chapter": {
    "number": 17,
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "The Burden against Damascus"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 1,
        "content": [
          "This is the burden against Damascus:",
          {
            "lineBreak": true
          },
          {
            "text": "“Behold, Damascus is no longer a city;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "it has become a heap of ruins.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 2,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The cities of Aroer are forsaken;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "they will be left to the flocks,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "which will lie down with no one to fear.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 3,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The fortress will disappear from Ephraim,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2577
          },
          {
            "text": "and the sovereignty from Damascus.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "The remnant of Aram will be",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "like the splendor of the Israelites,”",
            "poem": 2
          },
          "declares the LORD of Hosts."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 4,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "“In that day the splendor of Jacob will fade,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and the fat of his body will waste away,",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 5,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "as the reaper gathers the standing grain",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and harvests the ears with his arm,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "as one gleans heads of grain",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "in the Valley of Rephaim.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 6,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Yet gleanings will remain,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "like an olive tree that has been beaten—",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "two or three berries atop the tree,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "four or five on its fruitful branches,”",
            "poem": 2
          },
          "declares the LORD, the God of Israel."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 7,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "In that day men will look to their Maker",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and turn their eyes to the Holy One of Israel.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 8,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "They will not look to the altars",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "they have fashioned with their hands",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "or to the Asherahs and incense altars",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "they have made with their fingers.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 9,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "In that day their strong cities",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "will be like forsaken thickets and summits,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "abandoned to the Israelites",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and to utter desolation.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 10,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "For you have forgotten the God of your salvation",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and failed to remember the Rock of your refuge.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Therefore, though you cultivate delightful plots",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and set out cuttings from exotic vines—",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 11,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "though on the day you plant",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "you make them grow,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "and on that morning",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "you help your seed sprout—",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "yet the harvest will vanish",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "on the day of disease and incurable pain.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 12,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Alas, the tumult of many peoples;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "they rage like the roaring seas and clamoring nations;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "they rumble like the crashing of mighty waters.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 13,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The nations rage like the rush of many waters.",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "He rebukes them, and they flee far away,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "driven before the wind like chaff on the hills,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "like tumbleweeds before a gale.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 14,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "In the evening, there is sudden terror!",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "Before morning, they are no more!",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "This is the portion of those who loot us",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and the lot of those who plunder us.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      }
    ],
    "footnotes": [
      {
        "noteId": 2577,
        "caller": "+",
        "text": "Or The fortified city will disappear from Ephraim, that is, from the northern kingdom of Israel",
        "reference": {
          "chapter": 17,
          "verse": 3
        }
      }
    ]
